<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99365059562026></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99365059562026><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99365059562026>Wu's Tunic vs. Foreman's Tunic?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99365059562026#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=67705><span id=Sage>Kensuke</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>76 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jun 27th 10:03 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm curious about something. <br><br>Obviously the Foreman's Tunic is a better item to have then Wu's Fighting Tunic, simply because the stats are slightly better. <br><br>However, it seems odd to me that the tunic weighs NOTHING, and I'm assuming that this is just an oversight on Verant's part, and they haven't gotten around to fixing it yet, or simply don't know about the problem. <br><br>What's the official word on this from Verant? I'd hate to drop money on a Foreman's Tunic (and prices on my server seem to be above average... greedy bastards) only for it to be changed one day and suddenly weigh 6 pounds. <br><br>Also, while I'm comparing items, which would be better to have? An Orange Sash of Order from the Freeport Monk quest, or a thick leather apron? <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
