<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99365191260021></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99365191260021><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99365191260021>RE: Wu's Tunic vs. Foreman's Tunic?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99365191260021#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>171 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jun 27th 10:25 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.43]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The Foreman Tunic has been that way forever, it's the most popular mid-level monk tunic, and Verant knows all about it, I'm sure.  Don't worry about it being 'nerfed' -- just get one and be thankful that Verant gives monks a great tunic option for mid-levels.<br><br>Sad to say, the sashes and headbands are junk, except for their quest value towards the epic path.  They suddenly turn VERY valuable when you can turn them in for your RotLC in the mid-40s, but unless you are *really* into the roleplay value of wearing them, just keep them in the bank.<br><br>The thick leather apron is the way to go, by far.  You can wear it until you get your FBSS, also typically in your mid-40s.  I'm *finally* about to replace mine, as soon as I get into that Frenzy room and win a darn roll on the FBSS (could take a while).<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
