	   <tr><td colspan=2>Can't speak to the bread issue - I personally carry grapes for food (a stack weighs 0.1 lbs) and never took up baking.<br><br>Coins weigh 1 stone (or pound or whatever) per 40 - no matter what type.  So yes they weigh you down and eat up your AC.  I dump my coins into the bank as often as I can (I started in Qeynos and can run to the bank blindfolded at this point).  No need to keep cash on you once you've got enough food and water for the next couple days playing, or unless you're out to buy something.  When I bank, I only keep enough to pay for a teleport if that's in my plans.<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 46th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro <br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Strange Brew - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></tr>
