	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'll give you my progression - I am a little soft on the levels (it's been a while).  I stayed in Qeynos Hills and Blackburrow (plus a little Everfrost and a little Erud's crossing for wisps if memory serves) till my early teens.  I then relocated to Freeport, alternated my hunting between Oasis and Highpass Hold till around 19 or 20.  Went to South Karana and hunted Aviaks for a while (running back to high keep every so often to bank and resupply), and then Gnolls at the South K spires.  Did High Keep almost exclusively till low 30s after that.  Fought The Overthere through mid 30s, then really started to wander a lot after that.<br><br>There are so many options as to where you can raid after your early levels that I can't really recommend one over another.  I know what I did, and I know that there are zones as good as or better than those I chose for my hunting.  I would suggest you move to Freeport once you've gotten tired of Blackburrow.  Much more of the world is accessible from there.<br><br>I typically carry 40p on me when I resupply and head out for trips to Kunark or Velious.  The price of ports varies, and often I get a guildie to pop me over to Dreadlands, but sometimes it costs decent coin to get places without having to spend the time on the boat.  And so you know I took the boat till my early 40s, when I got to where I could more than pay for the port by fighting during the time I'd otherwise be on a boat.<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 46th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro<br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Strange Brew - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></tr>
