<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99364753561373></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99364753561373><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99364753561373>RE: What is best armor and weps for a teen monk?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99364753561373#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>171 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jun 27th 9:12 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK, just for my own amusement, and because the servers are down for patch, I'm going to try to put together a list of gear that is reasonably cheap, and should last a young monk a while.<br><br>As Keye said, your ability to get stuff is going to be related to your PP situation.  I, like Keye, tend to be broke a lot -- in my case, because I don't care to do non-Exp loot camps often, or to do things like try to sell 200DF belts.  On the other hand, if you're patient and want to hunt wisps for a week straight (or something similar), you can get a lot more PP in the teens than I ever had.<br><br>Prices below are about 'average' for my server -- more mature servers will probably be cheaper.  As Keye said, get a base of Cured Silk in all spots -- you can then swap out as you can afford other pieces.  Personally, I achieved this 'level' of gear in my high 20s, slowly upgrading from cured silk (Wu's wasn't available then, or I might have had this exact set at some point).<br><br>Earrings -- Orc Fang (100PP/pair)<br>Rings -- Gold Fire Wedding Rings (200PP/pair)<br>Neck -- *Ulthork Collar (100PP)<br>Face -- Splitpaw Hide Mask (10PP)<br>Head -- *Executioners Hood (125PP)<br>Wrists -- *Vox Bracers (150PP/pair)<br>Arms -- Wu's Sleeves (75PP)<br>Hands -- *Gem Inlaid Gauntlets (100PP)<br>Shoulders -- *Drolvarg Mantle (100PP)<br>Back -- Wu's Cloak (150PP)<br>Chest -- Foremans Tunic (150PP)<br>Belt -- *Thick Leather Apron (25PP)<br>Legs -- *Wu's Pantaloons (150PP)<br>Boots -- *Wu's Slippers (150PP)<br><br>Total value of set:  1,585 PP (assuming I can add)<br><br>Items with an asterisk are things I STILL wear at level 44.  You can see that you get a LOT of long-term value out of this set.  No individual item is more than 150PP (each GF wed ring is 100PP).  Are you likely to be able to get this set in your mid-teens? No. But hopefully, it will give you some idea of the direction to upgrade from Cured Silk as you level and get PP to spend.<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
