<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99377645189040></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99377645189040><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99377645189040>RE: What is best armor and weps for a teen monk?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99377645189040#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=27649><span id=Guru>Palarran</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>117 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jun 28th 9:00 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.43]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you're looking to upgrade from cured silk but can't afford wu's armor, you might consider crystalline silk armor in some places.  AC is similar to cured silk, and every piece has a small sv magic bonus.  Magic resistance is very, very important--most of the times that I've been legitimately killed as a monk (in other words, excluding deaths due to the bug with feign death) have been due to casters, typically being feared, charmed and/or blinded; other times casters have made timing a feign difficult since if I feign while a mob is casting on me, when the spell lands mobs will attack me again unless I resist the spell.<br><br>A quick comparison of cured silk/crystalline silk/wu's armor:<br><br>*Cap: AC 4 / AC 4 sv magic+2 / AC 5 agi+3<br>*Cloak: AC 4 / AC 4 sv magic+3 / AC 5 agi+4<br>Tunic: AC 8 / AC 7 sv magic+4 / AC 9 agi+5<br>Gorget: AC 3 / AC 2 sv magic+1 / AC 4 agi+2<br>Gloves: AC 4 / AC 3 sv magic+2 / AC 4<br>Mantle: AC 3 / AC 2 sv magic+2 / AC 4 agi+3<br>*Mask: AC 2 / AC 2 sv magic+1 / AC 3 agi+1<br>Pants: AC 5 / AC 4 sv magic+3 / AC 6 agi+4<br>Sandals: AC 4 / AC 3 sv magic+2 / AC 5 agi+2<br>Sash: AC 3 / AC 2 sv magic+2 / AC 4 agi+2<br>*Sleeves: AC 4 / AC 4 sv magic+2 / AC 5 agi+3<br>Wristband: AC 3 / AC 2 sv magic+2 / AC 4 agi+1<br><br>The slots marked with * are the ones where you can upgrade from cured silk to crystalline silk without losing any AC.  The other pieces are only 1 AC lower.  In some cases the loss of 1 AC might be well worth the sv magic bonus...<br><br>(I'm not sure what the going rates on crystalline silk armor are; I would expect them to be significantly lower than wu's armor, since it takes a lower skill, and no 6pp+200 mana from an enchanter vial of viscous mana--each piece uses just over 1pp in store bought components.  The crystalline silk is a bit harder to get though...)<br><br>A couple other notes...iksar monks can't use vox bracers, but unlike humans they can use a kunzar cloak (AC 7 wis+2 int+2 sv fire+10, wt 0.1).  Depending on your server the kunzar cloak might be more than 150pp, becoming more expensive than the items listed above, but not by too much.  Also, I've been very happy with my Fine Silk Turban (AC 10 sv fire+10, wt 0.3) for the head...cost me about 100pp if I remember right.  Again, your server's prices may vary.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
