	   <tr><td colspan=2>1HB should go up like a rocket at the lower levels -- When I was still using a Staff (at your level), it would take about one yellow bubble of exp for it to cap out (using 1HB in primary), then I would throw it back in the bank.  Something sounds very wrong with your 1HB situation.<br><br>Now, this is only something I have heard rumored, and never seen personally, BUT -- skills may be able to get bug-stuck and not move.  If you have been fighting with 1HB in primary for a long time without ANY movement, try putting ONE training point into it.  It's only one point, so you'll still have plenty for FD/ID, and maybe it will help get your skill moving again.<br><br>As for GLSs -- never sell to vendors.  The player market will be 6-8PP, which is good and convenient.  However, if you have bank room, try to save up a couple of backpacks in the bank, then head to North Karana with them.  In the Gypsy camp there, there is a female Gypsy who will give you a Concordance of Research in exchange for one GLS.  You can then sell the CoR to a Merchant for about 9PP.  Best way to max out your GLS income that I know of.<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
