<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99360120347212></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99360120347212><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99360120347212>RE: Next set of question? lol</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99360120347212#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>465 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jun 26th 8:20 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just my 2 cp here...<br><br>1)  I went to South Karana after High Pass and before High Keep.  You're a bit light, IMO, for High Keep at 20.  You can fight aviaks and gnolls in South K till 23 or so, then do High Keep till your low to mid 30s if you desire after that.<br><br>2)  Conventional wisdom, and I'm personally confirming it every day, is that you want things in this order...  AC, Resists, HP, Stats.  At higher levels, you're going to SERIOUSLY lag the tanks in HP.  I'm 46 and have 1100 hp unbuffed, and maybe up to 1700 buffed.  The tanks have twice that.  We're not meat shields, and we're no good if we have to feign out after a dozen hard hits, or 2-3 big mob nukes.  I've given up stats in favor of AC and resists on several items, and I find I stay healthier longer as a result, can contribute more to the melee, and sponge less healer mana.  And in any decent group I get buffs that crank my strength and agility up quite a bit.<br><br>3) Don't know the invigorate effect, but the monk's job is to dish damage.  Every monk in the universe wants an FBSS at a minimum, and I believe that a right-click item stacks with that.  If your tank is doing his job, he's eating the damage while you pound away on the mob.  More haste, more pounding.  The flip side is controlling aggro, and I'm now realizing that this has to be a major reason monks switch to big 2HB sticks in their 50s - haste them and they dish huge damage, but still won't taunt as hard as 2 quick 1hb's will.<br><br>Robe of the Lost Circle is doable in mid 40s, and I've seen Whistling Fists (RoTLC plus 2 items) on 49 monkeys.<br><br>4)  Get used to throwing away sp and cp.  As you level up they become irrelevant.  Loot one decent item worth a few hundred plat and all the cp you've thrown away in your life become meaningless.  Even a page or a rune is worth anywhere from 800 to 4000 cp - far more than you could save on a day's fighting.  <br><br>Some people manage to make money, others don't.  I've always struggled with money - I always seem to have another expensive 'must-have' in mind.  It's a sliding scale.  I remember when 50pp seemed like huge cash - now I need thousands for my next upgrades.  Maybe it's because I haven't hunted for money that much - some zones make you rich, others don't.<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 46th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro <br><br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Strange Brew - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></tr>
