<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99358658043984></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99358658043984><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99358658043984>RE: On the mend...</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99358658043984#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>171 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jun 26th 4:16 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This bug is due to lag, and hitting mend when your PC and the server are out of sync.  It actually used to be quite a bit worse (they put in a fix for it) -- now, I find it only happens rarely.<br><br>If you have been experiencing lag, especially if this bug has happened during a session , try waiting a few seconds before hitting mend.  Also, make sure the connection monitor shows 0% lag.  This will usually take care of the problem.<br><br>Note that if you zone after getting this bug, mend will refresh upon zoning, and you will NOT have to wait for a full cycle to try again.<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
