	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, the Sarnak Enforcer is a Kunark item - drops in Dalnir, and you're not quite old enough to handle that zone.  Keep trying, one will turn up.<br><br>As for your skill not going up, remember that skills are level capped - 1HB goes at lvl*5+5, so if you got to 70 at lvl 13, it wouldn't go up again till 14.  You should see some movement now.  Nothing special about the Sarnak Enforcer that would make your skills go up any faster - it's just a weapon that has a nice combination of stats and light weight (7/28 1.5 lbs vs 6/38 8.0 lbs).  If you can't find an Enforcer, ask around for a fine steel warhammer 6/30 7.3 lbs.  Shouldn't cost u more than 6 p (hell, I give them away sometimes) and it'll do you a bit better than the mace - till u find your enforcer.  Just keep at it.<br><br>Grats on the drolvarg mantle, by the way.  I still wear mine - great monk item.<br><br>Don't know if this is true on all servers, but on Druzzil Ro the market is so saturated that items are going for a quarter to a half of what Allakhazam lists.  Drolvarg mantles are going as cheap as 50 pp<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 46th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro <br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Strange Brew - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></tr>
