<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99349853018274></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99349853018274><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99349853018274>RE: Instill Doubt - oops</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99349853018274#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>465 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jun 25th 3:48 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.61]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Instill doubt is an attack - if you are in attack range and it fires, even on an NPC that is amiable to you, you'll get whomped.  Fortunately, as Osano noted, you can target a mob and attempt to ID from halfway across the zone.  You can also ID boats - if you can target it, you can ID.  If you have more skill points lying around, burn them and get ID to 40.  Should train up a lot faster from that point.  It is the hardest skill for monks to train up, it seems, so ID constantly - when travelling, in a group between mobs (target another player), when sitting in the EC tunnel selling.  In fact, unless you're trying to use it for real, try to always target a player - you won't get yourself killed.<br><br>Some monks consider ID a useless skill - I remember reading exactly those words when I was starting out.  In a dungeon, it can be lethal - so much so that I change the hotkey when I go to dungeons.  However, if you have a snarer around, it can be glorious in outdoor settings.  I've lately found it pretty effective for fear-kiting Drolvargs in Dreadlands - the dogs fear pretty easily, and if snared you can beat them with impugnity from behind.  Fearing an unsnared mob isn't productive unless you have SoW or just want to make it run away for a while, so pick and choose when you want to use it.<br><br>It's also worth noting that ID will always fail if you try to special attack before it 'fires.'  Monkly-Business.com has a good write up on how to use it properly.<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 46th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro <br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Strange Brew - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></tr>
