	   <tr><td colspan=2>Back to the merchants. <br><br>Some people try to sell fish rolls and muffins in far away zones where there aren't any merchants that sell food. Since fish rolls and muffins last longer then bread or rations. <br><br>I can see the merit to that, but I think it's faster to make money just sitting in front of a merchant, making fish fillets, and then selling them right back to him. <br><br>My normal strategy is to carry two backpacks and two sacks and a spit to either the merchant who sells fish or jugs of sauces. Once there, I fill up all my inventory slots with stacks of one component, making sure my spit stays empty, and that I leave two slots in one container. Then I just head to the other merchant, buy a stack from him, sell back the goods, buy another stack, sell back the goods, and when more inventory slots are freed up, I buy more stacks, until I'm out of all components, and 30 pp's richer. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
