	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Lvl 1-5: Newbie zones obviously. If you start in Freeport (which I did) at lvl 3 or so you can go to either EC or NRO grass areas. Hunt spiderlings, armadillos, fire beetles, coyotes etc. <br><br>Lvl 6-10: Travel down to Gfay and hunt orc hill to lvl 7 or 8. After this go to CB enterance and take the cents. Good exp and loot if you can take the weight penalty of holding money. <br><br>10-14: Travel back to Freeport and hunt dervs in North Ro. Great exp and loot, especially gems and bronze. Don't wory much about weight penalty at this points, as loot will definetly make up for it. I made about 100pp at this stage just looting bronze gems and gold silver and copper.<br><br>15-18: Oasis!!!! Great exp. At first get into a group of 2-3 peeps and hunt caimans crocs and the occasional deepwater caiman. At lvl 16-17 solo crocs and caimans and anything that cons blue or even black! If you have mend you will usually be able to fight off a black solo. And if worst comes to worst, you run to docks. Try to have a SoW at all times so you can always run. <br>     Also, a quick money making tip. Take time off from hunting crocs and caimans etc. and ask someone who is hunting Spectres if you can take their loot. They drop tons of words, but the most money comes from they scyths, either bronze (2.5pp each) or regular scythes (10pp each!<br><br>   Well I hope this helps you, and this is where I am on my journy, lvl 18. Also, save up lots of training points for Feign Death and Instill Doubt, I saved up since about lvl 6. And at lvl 10 put 1 point into Tiger Claw. Lvl 5 Round kick. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
