<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99322806638961></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99322806638961><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99322806638961>RE: Training points&money</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99322806638961#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>465 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jun 22nd 12:41 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.61]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Conventional wisdom seems to be that ID needs to be trained up to 40 so that you don't go berzerk from frustration in practicing it.  So, with that in mind, you'll need to save 22 points for ID when you get it next level.  Allowing for the 5 you get when you ding next, that leaves you with 48 points available for FD or other things.  I don't know how much it'll cost you to train FD up past the first few levels, and I don't recall how fast or slow money came to me at your level.  I'd say burn a bunch of points on FD, get it to 40 or 50 (depending on what it costs of course) - the time you'd spend training it up from nothing can be better used fighting and getting xp and making money, and it'll save your ass a million times.<br><br>As for whether you should shoot the moon on your skill points?  You want to have a good number of points available at 30 when you get Flying Kick.  It's a rokking attack, and you'll want to get it off to a good start.  Other than that I don't think there are skills you need to burn more than a point on from here on out - unless you've let something fundamental lag (like I did with 2HB).  Your Mend maxed?  You're close to where it'll always work (skill 100) - that's the only one I can think of burning additional points on.<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 45th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Strange Brew - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></tr>
